  "prompt": "How is Hired's referral rate?",
  "response": "Hired\u2019s referral rate can vary over time and may not be publicly disclosed in detail. The referral rate typically refers to the percentage of hires that come from referrals made by current employees or by existing candidates. If you're looking for specific statistics about Hired's referral rate, it would be best to check their official website, social media channels, or contact their support for the most up-to-date information. Additionally, industry reports or surveys focused on recruitment platforms may provide some insights into trends related to referral rates in the hiring industry.",
